The article is a statement by the President and the First Lady expressing their condolences on the passing of Nancy Reagan. They acknowledge her role as a former First Lady and how she redefined the position during her time in the White House. They also mention her advocacy for Alzheimer's disease and her efforts to improve and save lives through treatment. The President and First Lady offer their sincere condolences to Nancy Reagan's children and grandchildren and express gratitude for her guidance and pray that she is reunited with her husband.